caption: Great sushi! Tastes so fresh and surpassed expectations for our first time ordering from here! Highly recommend.
Delicious spicy Ramen and fun presentation of mochi!
My go-to place for sushi in Lakeview. The employees are very nice and the prices are reasonable. Getting a complementary bowl of Miso soup with my order is also a nice touch.

The edamame and gyoza were fresh, and VERY reasonably priced during happy hour. The free Miso soup was a nice bonus. The fish was fresh and the sushi was handcrafted with care. Alcohol was reasonably priced, but they also offered BYOB. Staff was friendly and didn’t rush the meal. Overall a great dining experience.
Definitely a great place and fantastic service. The sushi was super tasty too so I definitely recommend.
Reviewing during COVID 19 pandemic: we have ordered out a few times from this place. Affordable, decent sushi. It’s a simple unpretentious place with consistent quality sushi.

I would like to make a review on the food but our order was never fulfilled despite waiting an hour and a half with no updates via the Caviar app. I understand businesses are working through how to respond in Covid times, but if you can’t fulfill orders then you need to disable the online ordering apps until you have availability to fulfill the orders. The Caviar support peeps could also not get ahold of them because their phone was off the hook. I hope they can figure out a better system and perhaps I’ll be able to try the food someday.
Best japanese food my wife and I have had in Lakeview thus far

Have ordered delivery 5+ times and this place is FIRE. The spicy tuna roll is delicious because the actual tuna is spicy — not some globbed on sauce that makes it “spicy” like some other restaurants. The bulgogi is classic and tender. The chicken wings are amazing especially for delivery! Hot and saucy/sticky. This is the only spot I’ll order sushi from.

Incredibly good sushi, and I cannot emphasize enough how the prices cannot be beat, especially during happy hour. Some sushi places try to feed you lots of rice or old sushi, but not this place! Sakae Sushi is the greatest sushi place I've ever been to in my life, and my only regret is that I live so far away. I'm going to be moving in this upcoming fall, and you better believe I will be moving somewhere closer to Sakae Sushi. That's how great this restaurant is. It is literally impacting my moving decisions. You will not regret trying this place.
Great sushi spot with late night hour. Reasonable price. Friendly staffs, good quality of sushi. Totally recommend!
Also leave with a smile! Staff is always on their A game and cudos to the chef for the sushi he sends from his kitchen, absolutely amazing!
Great and delightful food, I love the mood the spot has, and the employees were friendly. I will definitely visit here again.

I had my favorite sushi ever here. The prices are more than affordable. I'm not a huge sushi fan but it must be since I had never had sushi this good. They also have chicken wings that were super tasty as well. BYOB is a big plus too!
An East Lakeview gem. Friendly service, great prices, and delicious food. BYOB and don’t miss the happy hour deals too!
Great prices and tasty
The food here is so delicious. The prices are really good. I highly recommend this place to anyone who loves sushi!!
Excelente food and service
Soooooo good!
Sushi was alright. There are a lot of really good sushi places nearby, so I guess I was a little disappointed. I will say, the miso soup is free and tastes great!
The food here is amazing ! First time trying and it was worth it!
Amazing sushi spot. One of favs. Quality seafood and moderate pricing. Staff was friendly and ambiance was excellent.
My favorite place and one of the best sushi place in Chicago thanks chef Tom

This is a great sushi place that serves traditional sushi where flavor of the fish is presented foremost and not drowned in sugary fatty sauce.  It's one of my favorite sushi places in Chicago.  Calm, relaxed atmosphere, good for romantic date or if you want to talk during dinner.
The appetizers were absolutely fantastic! Best miso soup, and pot stickers I've ever had, hands down! Wish I could say the same about their sushi rolls, though.
Such good sushi and our server, El, was amazing and so sweet!
So my friend took me here for dinner and the food was really good. She didn't like kherheb him but this sake was served perfectly.

Great food and great service!  Very nice atmosphere. Amaizing presentation of all the dishes! Came here with my whole family and wasn’t disappointed. Definitely will be coming back and would recommend to my friends.
Everything was fresh and delicious awesome service and great ambience
Our server Elvina is friendly professional and nice. If i could choose I would give it 6:)

The food is great, original taste and design made it a for sure 5 star place for me! Water bottles are really enjoyable, service is adorable and sweet. Planning to celebrate Father’s Day with my family there

I never usually leave reviews for restaurants, but I've been walking past this place for months now and finally decided to give it a try and MAN I’m glad I did. I ordered the Spicy Shrimp Tempura Udon and the K2 Roll for delivery. The Udon was nicely packaged so none of the tempura was soggy and definitely lived up to the “spicy” of its name! So yummy. K2 Roll had three different colors of Roe which was mostly just fun for me as a lover of roe. The fish was great quality and the portion was pretty good for the price. Both items were incredibly delicious. I’m so glad to have found my new favorite sushi place in Lakeview!
I hope everyone will come to sakae sushi! The Korean style Chicken wings are amazing!! And spicy shrimp tempura udon is great! I think it is good for with hot sakae This place is heaven
Bomb sushi, open late, friendly staff. Win.
Good choices of ramen and the sushi had a great taste to it! This was a great quiet sushi experience
Friendly staff, no wait, and they have soju! They take reservations as well.
It's ok
The sushi was fresh and delicious!!! Can't wait to go backl!

This new place in north definitely gives a tough competition to the already existing sushi place.The sushi was definitely very good and the prices were competitive.My favorite was The Windy City, followed by Kamikaze, California rolls.They have free Miso soup which was my favorite,  cause free food.The place is very cozy,the staff was extremely friendly, and the service was quick. Try their mochi collection.And yeah, they are BYOB.!!!
Great service and great food
Decent sushi for a reasonable price. The yellowtail is delicious.
Great place for a date night. Service was spot on. Very attentive to the table. Will be going back.

Great service and reasonable price. The portions were generous and I ordered way too much. #4Rolls Our waitress was nice and offered to refrigerate our wine rather than charge us the extra $2 for an ice bucket
Good and open late.

First time visiting— had an incredible experience with a close group of friends. We all agreed that this was one of the best sushi establishments we had been to. The quality and freshness of the sushi we ordered was unparalleled.
The food here is 🔥🔥🔥!! Love it

Fantastic little sushi bar. Great service and awesome flavor. I'm a little reluctant to publish my review because I don't want to give away the secret. But if you're in East Lake view, check this place out.
Simply excellent service and taste for a neighborhood sushi spot. Family owned and the husband and wife are so lovely with a smile. Highly recommended this place.

Beginning to end this was an amazing experience. Nick greeted us with such warmth that immediately made you feel at home, he explained a couple of things to us and seeing how knowledgeable he was we decided to let him guide our night. He knew exactly what to bring us from the gyoza to the sashimi to the sake we drank and the mochi and green tea ice cream that finished us off. The cuts of fish were so fresh. The salmon felt like butter in my mouth and the tuna was soft as well. Honestly can't ask for more of a sushi place than this. If you decide to stop by give their hot and spicy chicken wings a chance too, they are fire. I was so full and couldn't think of eating more but when I smelled the wing I definitely knew I had to make room to taste it. Overall a great experience will definitely be coming back soon!
Excellent vegetarian menu, great service and prices. :) Loved the atmosphere - we were there for a while.
I was in Chicago for a night and I really enjoyed my dinner there, the price and quality of the food was excellent
Excellent food and service...transported me right back to Tokyo. Authentic and quality cuisine, with care and passion from the restaurant team, especially Nick! Follow his recommendations!!
Great food. Highly recommend.
Some of the best sushi I've had in Chicago at a very reasonable price. The quality of the fish is top notch, as is the service.
Wings are fuego! I got the sakae and alligator rolls and loved them both. !
so good. so fast. the sushi is fresh and delicious and beautifully made. the wings will change your life. i’m serious. life changing wings.
This place is amazing. Excellent quality fish, good atmosphere, and great service. Prices are really good for the quality of the food.
Excellent quality and good prices. Welcoming atmosphere that's great for a comfortable night out or a special occasion.
